# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics on the STEM Compass website. The analytics script has been added to all HTML pages to enable visitor tracking and page view analytics.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
1. **index.html** - Added Vercel Web Analytics script
2. **about.html** - Added Vercel Web Analytics script
3. **quiz.html** - Added Vercel Web Analytics script
4. **portal.html** - Added Vercel Web Analytics script
5. **chatbot.html** - Added Vercel Web Analytics script

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the Vercel Web Analytics guide for plain HTML sites. The following script was added to the `<head>` section of each HTML file, just before the closing `</head>` tag:

```html
<script>
    window.va = window.va || function () { (window.vaq = window.vaq || []).push(arguments); };
</script>
<script defer src="/_vercel/insights/script.js"></script>
```

### Why This Approach?

Since this is a plain HTML website (not using frameworks like Next.js, React, or Vue), the HTML implementation was the appropriate choice as specified in the Vercel Web Analytics documentation. This approach:

- Does not require installing the `@vercel/analytics` package
- Works immediately once the site is deployed to Vercel
- Automatically tracks page views across all pages
- Loads the analytics script asynchronously with the `defer` attribute to avoid blocking page rendering

## Next Steps

After deploying to Vercel:

1. **Enable Web Analytics** in the Vercel dashboard:
   - Go to your project in the Vercel dashboard
   - Click the **Analytics** tab
   - Click **Enable** to activate Web Analytics

2. **Verify Installation**:
   - Once deployed, visit any page of the site
   - Open browser DevTools > Network tab
   - Look for a request to `/_vercel/insights/view`
   - If you see this request, analytics is working correctly

3. **View Analytics Data**:
   - Return to the Vercel dashboard after a few visits
   - Click the **Analytics** tab to view visitor data
   - Filter and analyze page views, visitor counts, and more

## Notes

- No package manager dependencies needed for this implementation
- Analytics will only work when deployed to Vercel (not in local development)
- The `/_vercel/insights/*` routes will be automatically created by Vercel upon deployment
- Privacy-compliant: Vercel Web Analytics does not use cookies and respects user privacy
